OPENAI_API_KEY is not set; dry-run only.\")\n64615:    _die(\"OPENAI_API_KEY is not set. Export it before running.\")\n68330:- \"Where should I create this skill? If you do not have a preference, I will place it in `$CODEX_HOME/skills` (or `~/.codex/skills` when `CODEX_HOME` is unset) so Codex can discover it automatically.\"\n68350:Before running `init_skill.py`, ask where the user wants the skill created. If they do not specify a location, default to `$CODEX_HOME/skills`; when `CODEX_HOME` is unset, fall back to `~/.codex/skills` so the skill is auto-discovered.\n68357:scripts/init_skill.py my-skill --path \"${CODEX_HOME:-$HOME/.codex}/skills\"\n68358:scripts/init_skill.py my-skill --path \"${CODEX_HOME:-$HOME/.codex}/skills\" --resources scripts,references\n69219:description: Install Codex skills into $CODEX_HOME/skills from a curated list or a GitHub repo path. Use when a user asks to list installable skills, install a curated skill, or install a skill from another repo (including private repos).\n69249:- Installs into `$CODEX_HOME/skills/<skill-name>` (defaults to `~/.codex/skills`).\n69257:- Installed annotations come from `$CODEX_HOME/skills`.\n69301:\"\"\"Install a skill from a GitHub repo path into $CODEX_HOME/skills.\"\"\"\n69334:    return os.environ.get(\"CODEX_HOME\", os.path.expanduser(\"~/.codex\"))\n69579:    return os.environ.get(\"CODEX_HOME\", os.path.expanduser(\"~/.codex\"))\n70748:` not found. Defaulting to fallback metadata; this can degrade performance and cause issues.usage limitedlimited by budgetObjective: Time used: Tokens used: Token budget: Commands: /goal edit, /goal pause, /goal clearCommands: /goal edit, /goal resume, /goal clearCommands: /goal edit, /goal clearEdit goalType a goal objective and press EnterResume paused goal?Resume goalMark it active and continue when idleLeave pausedKeep it paused; use /goal resume laterevent tui/src/onboarding/onboarding_screen.rs:140codex_tui::onboarding::onboarding_screentui/src/onboarding/onboar